data.name: instructionsList.Text
data.value:
Registers (REG): AX --> AH, AL BX --> BH, BL CX --> CH, CL DX --> DH, DL
Stack Pointer --> SP Base Pointer --> BP Instruction Pointer --> IP Source Index --> SI Destination Index --> DI
Flags: SF --> Signal Flag ZF --> Zero Flag PF --> Parity Flag AF --> Auxiliary Carry Flag CF --> Carry Flag OF --> Overflow Flag IF --> Interrupt Flag DF --> Direction Flag TF --> Trap Flag
Memeory --> mem
8086 INSTRUCTIONS: -------------------------------------------------------------- MOV { REG, value/REG/mem } Copy operand_2 to operand_1.
PUSH { REG[AX, BX, CX, DX]/value } Push data to stack.
POP { REG[AX, BX, CX, DX] } Delete last value on stack.
PUSHF { - } Push higher and lower byte to stack.
POPF { - } Delete from top of the stack higher and lower byte.
XCHG { REG, REG } Change operand_2 with operand_1.
LEA { REG, mem } Load Effective Address.
LAHF { - } Load AH from 8 low bits of Flags register.
SAHF { - } Store AH in to Flags.
ADD { REG/mem/value, REG/mem/value } Addition
SUB { REG/mem/value, REG/mem/value } Subtraction
MUL { REG/mem } Multiplication
DIV { REG/mem } Division
INC { REG } Increment
DEC { REG } Decrement
AAA { - } Ascii adjust after addition.
AAS { - } Asci adjust after subtraction.
IMUL { REG/mem } Multiplication of Signed Numbers.
IDEC { REG/mem } Division of Signed Number.
NOT { REG/mem } Negation
AND { REG/mem, REG/mem }
OR { REG/mem, REG/mem }
XOR { REG/mem, REG/mem }
CLC { - } Clear Carry Flag.
CLD { - } Clear Direction Flag.
CLI { - } Clear Interrupt Flag.
STC { - } Set Carry Flag.
STD { - } Set Direction Flag.
STI { - } Set Interrupt Flag.
CMC { - } Complement Carry Flag.

data.name: info.Text
data.value: The application presents a simplified simulator of the Intel 8086 microprocessor from 1978. It has the basic instructions of this processor (MOV, ADD, SUB, PUSH, POP). The processor accepts one instruction described on the buttons and from zero to 2 operands in the appropriate format (names of registers written in capital letters). After inserting ";" subsequent characters will not be considered. The application was created for the "school" project.
